# Learning Process

## 1. Feynman Technique

### Answer to Question 1
- It means explaining a concept in very simple words  
- You teach it as if the other person knows nothing  
- If you can explain it clearly, you truly understand it  
- It helps you find weak points  
- It makes learning easier


## 2. Learning How to Learn (Barbara Oakley TED Talk)

### Answer to Question 2
- Barbara was very bad at math when young  
- She avoided math because she thought she couldnâ€™t learn it  
- Later she learned it slowly with the right techniques  
- She trained her brain step-by-step  
- She became an engineering professor  
- It shows anyone can learn difficult things with proper methods

### Answer to Question 3
- Thinking has two modes  
- Active Mode = full focus, step-by-step thinking  
- You solve problems directly in this mode  
- Diffused Mode = relaxed, open thinking  
- Ideas come naturally when your mind is free  
- You often get insights while walking or resting


## 3. Learn Anything in 20 Hours

### Answer to Question 4
- Break the skill into small parts  
- Learn just enough to start practicing  
- Remove distractions  
- Practice for at least 20 hours  
- Improve through repetition  
- Fix mistakes as you practice


## 4. Improving Your Learning Process

### Answer to Question 5
- Keep your phone away  
- Remove distractions  
- Use deep-work sessions  
- Explain concepts in simple words  
- Practice by writing code  
- Track your time daily  
- Ask questions when confused  
- Stay consistent  
- Make learning enjoyable  
- Teach someone to check your understanding
